on Federation of Churches; Treasurer, Interracial Committee, under chairmanship of Dr. Charles Edward Russell.  Charter member of the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People.  Named as one of the \"\"one hundred most famous alumni\"\" of Oberlin College at its one hundredth anniversary, 1933*  Received a citation for social service at the Women's Centennial Congress, New York, November 1940.  Author, \"\"A Colored Woman in a White World\"\" (published 1940), with preface by H. G. Wells.  (See also \"\"Who's Who in America.\"\")")
